Mmm!

1:09:27.914 --> 1:09:29.290
Something smells good.

1:09:29.332 --> 1:09:31.542
One of my family's secret recipes.

1:09:31.584 --> 1:09:33.837
Something my aunt used to make.

1:09:36.714 --> 1:09:38.133
Tom and the kids are...?

1:09:38.174 --> 1:09:40.176
On a walk, I think.

1:09:43.013 --> 1:09:44.722
Oh, babe! Oh, no.

1:09:44.764 --> 1:09:46.641
Let me help you.

1:09:46.683 --> 1:09:48.601
Put it down.

1:09:48.643 --> 1:09:50.520
Let's be very careful.

1:09:50.561 --> 1:09:52.605
Look. Ta-da!

1:09:55.608 --> 1:09:57.276
[Mary chuckles]

1:09:58.653 --> 1:10:00.488
No more E.R. visits.

1:10:01.948 --> 1:10:03.199
Let me get you some chili.

1:10:03.240 --> 1:10:04.534
Okay.

1:10:12.333 --> 1:10:13.793
Mmm.

1:10:13.835 --> 1:10:15.670
Do you know how beautiful you are?

1:10:15.712 --> 1:10:17.088
[chuckles]

1:10:19.132 --> 1:10:20.717
Did you know that

1:10:20.758 --> 1:10:24.303
tomorrow is my and Tom's anniversary?

1:10:24.345 --> 1:10:26.681
I hope when I'm older I look as good as you.

1:10:26.723 --> 1:10:29.517
[laughs] Ten years!

1:10:29.559 --> 1:10:31.561
Did you hear me, Mary?

1:10:33.479 --> 1:10:34.772
I bought a new dress,

1:10:34.814 --> 1:10:36.566
it's black and it's backless.

1:10:36.607 --> 1:10:37.692
I hope he likes it.

1:10:37.734 --> 1:10:38.985
Mary.

1:10:39.027 --> 1:10:40.611
Please.

1:10:41.696 --> 1:10:43.322
You deserve this.

1:10:49.871 --> 1:10:51.081
[gasps]

1:10:55.334 --> 1:10:56.586
[Grace moans]

1:10:58.171 --> 1:10:59.630
[breathing heavily]

1:11:00.590 --> 1:11:01.883
[Grace] Oh!

1:11:02.842 --> 1:11:04.385
[heartbeat]

1:11:07.055 --> 1:11:09.099
[Grace] Ahh...

1:11:09.140 --> 1:11:10.725
-[door opens] -[Sam] Mom?

1:11:12.018 --> 1:11:13.436
[door closes]

1:11:13.477 --> 1:11:15.688
Hey, it smells great! What's cooking?

1:11:15.730 --> 1:11:18.315
-Yeah, I'm starving. -[Sam] Me, too.

1:11:18.357 --> 1:11:22.570
I--I'm just suddenly not feeling so great, baby.

1:11:22.612 --> 1:11:24.739
I think I'm just gonna go lay down, okay?

1:11:24.781 --> 1:11:26.157
I'll get you some water.

1:11:26.199 --> 1:11:28.034
[Mary] Thanks, honey.

1:11:28.076 --> 1:11:30.453
Hey, guys, how was the park?

1:11:31.579 --> 1:11:32.747
[groans]

1:11:37.127 --> 1:11:38.544
[Tom] Here you go.

1:11:38.586 --> 1:11:39.921
I love you, babe.

1:11:39.963 --> 1:11:42.381
Mm, love you more.

1:11:46.219 --> 1:11:48.012
[sighs]

1:11:49.139 --> 1:11:50.473
Tom.

1:12:18.251 --> 1:12:20.503
[Grace, distant] Not that hard, you idiot!

1:12:22.005 --> 1:12:23.756
[indistinct distant yelling]

1:12:27.885 --> 1:12:29.220
[Grace moans]

1:12:32.640 --> 1:12:35.601
[Tom and Grace moaning]

1:12:43.818 --> 1:12:45.320
[moaning continues]

1:12:49.991 --> 1:12:51.534
[Grace] Slower!

1:12:52.743 --> 1:12:54.745
[Tom and Grace breathing heavily]

1:12:56.289 --> 1:12:57.790
[Grace] There.

1:12:57.832 --> 1:12:59.334
Oh, that's it.

1:13:00.918 --> 1:13:03.838
[both panting, moaning]

1:13:05.756 --> 1:13:06.966
[Grace] Now!

1:13:17.685 --> 1:13:20.479
Oh, that's a good boy.

1:13:29.030 --> 1:13:30.531
Who's in charge?

1:13:31.991 --> 1:13:34.869
I said, who's in charge

1:13:34.911 --> 1:13:37.747
and will always be in charge?!

1:13:47.006 --> 1:13:48.674
[Grace] Don't worry,

1:13:48.716 --> 1:13:50.593
she won't remember any of this.

1:14:20.623 --> 1:14:22.041
[Tom] You feeling better?

1:14:22.083 --> 1:14:23.960
Yeah, sort of, yeah.

1:14:24.001 --> 1:14:26.212
Just had a horrible dream.

1:14:28.172 --> 1:14:30.300
Sam, Alex, time for dinner.

1:14:33.469 --> 1:14:35.512
Come on, take your seat.

1:14:35.554 --> 1:14:37.098
No more video games.

1:14:40.684 --> 1:14:42.937
Well, as long as you survived your dream,

1:14:42.979 --> 1:14:44.272
that's all that matters.

1:14:47.900 --> 1:14:51.154
[Mary] Um, Grace, uh...

1:14:52.696 --> 1:14:55.241
I seem to remember you saying that

1:14:55.283 --> 1:14:57.660
this was sacred family time.

1:14:57.701 --> 1:14:59.078
So...

1:14:59.120 --> 1:15:01.580
what the hell are you still doing here?

1:15:01.622 --> 1:15:04.041
[Tom] What are you saying? What are you talking about?

1:15:04.083 --> 1:15:05.501
Um, she's right.

1:15:07.086 --> 1:15:08.879
Must have been a pretty awful dream.

1:15:08.921 --> 1:15:11.299
Teacher says a bad dream is actually a nightmare.

1:15:11.341 --> 1:15:13.550
You and my husband

1:15:13.592 --> 1:15:15.136
-were fucking! -[Tom] Mary!

1:15:15.178 --> 1:15:17.054
Over there, on the counter!

1:15:17.096 --> 1:15:18.722
-Damn it! -It was so real!

1:15:18.764 --> 1:15:20.350
It was so real!

1:15:20.391 --> 1:15:22.518
And you were like a totally different person,

1:15:22.559 --> 1:15:23.894
you were like somebody else.

1:15:23.936 --> 1:15:26.189
[Alex] Daddy, Mommy's scaring me.

1:15:26.230 --> 1:15:27.690
[Tom] I know honey,

1:15:27.731 --> 1:15:29.150
Mommy's not feeling very well.

1:15:29.192 --> 1:15:31.027
I think you need to go back and rest.

1:15:31.068 --> 1:15:33.237
[crying] You guys, I'm sorry.

1:15:33.279 --> 1:15:35.739
I'm really sorry.

1:15:38.242 --> 1:15:39.660
When Mommy writes,

1:15:39.702 --> 1:15:43.164
sometimes the things in her mind are so vivid

1:15:43.206 --> 1:15:45.791
that she can't tell the difference between

1:15:45.833 --> 1:15:48.752
the imaginary and the real.

1:15:54.800 --> 1:15:56.760
What happened to you out there?

1:15:56.802 --> 1:15:58.637
[Mary] I don't know.

1:15:58.679 --> 1:16:00.973
I'm not really sure.

1:16:08.147 --> 1:16:10.900
[sighs] Actually--

1:16:13.569 --> 1:16:15.321
I do know, actually.

1:16:16.364 --> 1:16:17.823
You know that nightmare?

1:16:19.616 --> 1:16:21.952
That's really how I feel about us.

1:16:21.994 --> 1:16:23.538
That's how I feel about you,

1:16:23.579 --> 1:16:25.456
that's how I feel about everything.

1:16:25.498 --> 1:16:28.501
Because for the longest time,

1:16:28.543 --> 1:16:31.462
I've just been sitting in the backseat

1:16:31.504 --> 1:16:33.506
and I've been letting you drive.

1:16:33.548 --> 1:16:34.840
And I've been supporting you

1:16:34.882 --> 1:16:37.510
in everything that you wanted to do.

1:16:37.552 --> 1:16:41.514
And I've been taking all of my energies and all of my talents,

1:16:41.556 --> 1:16:43.682
and pouring them into you

1:16:43.724 --> 1:16:46.727
and into the kids and into this life.

1:16:46.769 --> 1:16:49.939
Because I wanted to build something together.

1:16:49.980 --> 1:16:52.442
And what do I get for it?!

1:16:52.483 --> 1:16:54.651
What do I get for it?!

1:16:54.693 --> 1:16:56.487
Fucking screwed!

1:16:56.529 --> 1:16:58.697
You betrayed me!

1:16:58.739 --> 1:17:00.616
-You crash us into a wall -Come on, Mary--

1:17:00.657 --> 1:17:02.159
-and then, and then -Mary--

1:17:02.201 --> 1:17:05.204
you expect me to pick up the pieces

1:17:05.246 --> 1:17:06.914
and make everything better again!

1:17:06.956 --> 1:17:08.624
-Mary, I'm sorry. -No!

1:17:08.665 --> 1:17:10.418
-Come here. -No, don't comfort me!

1:17:10.460 --> 1:17:11.961
-Come here. -Don't comfort me!

1:17:12.002 --> 1:17:13.463
I'm sorry!

1:17:13.504 --> 1:17:15.256
I'm sorry, I fucked up.

1:17:15.298 --> 1:17:17.967
But you're my world, you're everything to me.

1:17:18.008 --> 1:17:19.676
You and the twins.

1:17:22.597 --> 1:17:25.099
I want to find a way to make it up to you.

1:17:25.141 --> 1:17:26.934
I promise, I will.

1:17:26.976 --> 1:17:29.228
And you're right, we're never gonna

1:17:29.270 --> 1:17:32.064
-live like that again. -No! You're damn straight!

1:17:32.106 --> 1:17:33.566
Yeah.

1:17:34.775 --> 1:17:36.611
-You mean everything to me. -[sniffs]

1:17:36.652 --> 1:17:39.530
Come on. You're almost through.

1:17:39.572 --> 1:17:41.616
Just let's not let this thing

1:17:41.657 --> 1:17:44.410
kill us on the way out.

1:17:44.452 --> 1:17:47.371
-All right. Yeah. [sniffs] -Okay?

1:18:18.277 --> 1:18:20.571
[laughter echoes]

1:20:44.298 --> 1:20:47.426
-Happy anniversary. -Happy anniversary.

1:20:52.931 --> 1:20:54.850
I'm gonna head in early today.

1:20:54.891 --> 1:20:57.144
-Rendezvous tonight? -Yeah.

1:21:06.320 --> 1:21:09.114
[Mary into phone] Oh, hi, this is Mary Morrison.

1:21:09.156 --> 1:21:12.368
I'm calling about a check that I sent in a while ago,

1:21:12.409 --> 1:21:14.578
but it seems like it hasn't been deposited yet.

1:21:14.620 --> 1:21:16.288
[woman] Oh, hi, Mrs. Morrison,

1:21:16.330 --> 1:21:17.748
I've been meaning to call you.

1:21:17.790 --> 1:21:20.417
Yes, I have your check right here.

1:21:20.459 --> 1:21:22.252
I was just waiting to hear

1:21:22.294 --> 1:21:24.463
which caregiver you want to go with.

1:21:25.715 --> 1:21:26.965
What?

1:21:27.007 --> 1:21:29.051
I should have called you sooner,

1:21:29.092 --> 1:21:30.969
I'm sorry, we've been terribly busy.

1:21:32.221 --> 1:21:33.514
Um...

1:21:36.433 --> 1:21:38.435
[quietly] Grace.

1:21:38.477 --> 1:21:40.020
You have a Grace, right?

1:21:41.438 --> 1:21:43.982
Sorry, we don't have anybody by that name.

1:21:45.984 --> 1:21:47.069
Mary?

1:21:47.110 --> 1:21:49.655
Um, okay, thank you.

1:21:49.697 --> 1:21:52.032
Thank you so much. Thank you for letting me know

1:21:52.074 --> 1:21:55.369
that it will be deposited soon. Okay, bye-bye.

1:21:57.120 --> 1:21:59.331
I was thinking of changing the master bedroom sheets.

1:21:59.373 --> 1:22:01.250
Since it's your anniversary.

1:22:04.253 --> 1:22:05.880
Yes, of course.

1:22:05.921 --> 1:22:07.798
Grace, I--

1:22:09.091 --> 1:22:11.385
I just want to apologize about last night.

1:22:11.427 --> 1:22:14.889
I really don't know what came over me.

1:22:14.930 --> 1:22:16.932
I think I had a fever.

1:22:16.973 --> 1:22:18.601
I understand.

1:22:18.642 --> 1:22:21.520
Nightmares can feel so real sometimes.

1:22:31.655 --> 1:22:35.117
If this were a library, I would check it out.

1:22:35.158 --> 1:22:36.952
[Mary] Well, if you like that one,

1:22:36.993 --> 1:22:38.579
follow me.

1:22:54.010 --> 1:22:57.765
She's your best friend and you don't even know her last name?

1:22:57.807 --> 1:22:59.809
I do know a book she checked out recently

1:22:59.850 --> 1:23:02.812
is Laddie, by Gene Stratton-Porter.

1:23:02.853 --> 1:23:04.146
Ah.

1:23:04.187 --> 1:23:05.815
[typing]

1:23:11.487 --> 1:23:13.864
The only person to check out Laddie

1:23:13.906 --> 1:23:16.492
in the last three months.

1:23:16.533 --> 1:23:18.911
Elaine, please, please call me back,

1:23:18.953 --> 1:23:20.537
I need to talk to you.

1:23:21.747 --> 1:23:23.039
[sighs]

1:23:52.319 --> 1:23:54.112
[buzzes]

1:24:00.452 --> 1:24:02.078
[knocks] Elaine?

1:24:02.120 --> 1:24:03.580
[latch clicks]

1:24:05.624 --> 1:24:08.335
Oh! Thank God, here you are!

1:24:08.377 --> 1:24:09.628
I've been trying to call you!

1:24:09.670 --> 1:24:11.588
You would not believe-- [gasps]

1:24:21.139 --> 1:24:23.642
[gasps, screams]

1:24:23.684 --> 1:24:25.268
Oh, my God!

1:24:28.355 --> 1:24:30.357
[gasping]

1:24:32.902 --> 1:24:35.988
Ah! Oh! 911!

1:24:36.030 --> 1:24:37.781
Please hurry!

1:24:37.823 --> 1:24:40.158
Please come! Oh, my God!

1:24:51.962 --> 1:24:53.213
[distant sirens]

1:24:59.177 --> 1:25:01.179
[crying]

1:25:03.682 --> 1:25:05.851
Mrs. Morrison.

1:25:05.893 --> 1:25:07.978
Would you mind coming down to the station

1:25:08.020 --> 1:25:09.145
to answer a few questions?

1:25:09.187 --> 1:25:11.815
Of course, whatever you need.

1:25:11.857 --> 1:25:14.359
Your husband's going to meet us there, okay?

1:25:14.401 --> 1:25:16.319
-Okay. -Okay.

1:25:32.502 --> 1:25:34.797
[officer] Pretty much an open and shut case.

1:25:37.132 --> 1:25:38.675
[officer #2 sighs]

1:25:40.510 --> 1:25:44.347
So... a writer, then.

1:25:44.389 --> 1:25:47.977
Mm-hmm, yes. Yes, I'm a writer. Um...

1:25:48.018 --> 1:25:50.938
Is my husband here yet? I'd really love to see him.

1:25:50.980 --> 1:25:52.689
He's on his way, Mrs. Morrison.

1:25:52.731 --> 1:25:54.399
In the meantime,

1:25:54.441 --> 1:25:56.944
you mind telling me what medications you're taking?

1:25:56.986 --> 1:25:59.613
Any kind of psychosis you may have been diagnosed with?

1:26:00.781 --> 1:26:02.032
Wh-What?

1:26:03.784 --> 1:26:04.868
What is this?

1:26:04.910 --> 1:26:06.662
We have footage of you, Mary.

1:26:06.703 --> 1:26:08.664
Early this morning, around 1:00 am,

1:26:08.705 --> 1:26:11.041
driving to the location of the deceased.

1:26:12.626 --> 1:26:14.294
That's not possible.

1:26:14.336 --> 1:26:16.922
And the deceased is my friend and her name is Elaine.

1:26:16.964 --> 1:26:19.091
We also have a witness, a neighbor of yours,

1:26:19.133 --> 1:26:21.468
saying you and Elaine were in some sort of argument

1:26:21.510 --> 1:26:23.219
yesterday evening outside your home.

1:26:23.261 --> 1:26:25.430
Do I need a lawyer present? Because I thought I was

1:26:25.472 --> 1:26:27.975
just coming here to help you with the investigation.

1:26:28.017 --> 1:26:30.686
And we have your fingerprints on the murder weapon.

1:26:30.727 --> 1:26:32.771
The scissors Elaine were stabbed with.

1:26:32.813 --> 1:26:34.648
That's just not possible.

1:26:35.858 --> 1:26:39.695
Mary, the evidence is all pointing one way.

1:26:39.736 --> 1:26:41.697
You either tell me something I don't know,

1:26:41.738 --> 1:26:43.406
or I'll lay it out for you.

1:27:01.216 --> 1:27:02.592
That could be anyone.

1:27:02.634 --> 1:27:04.761
We found this too, among your belongings

1:27:04.803 --> 1:27:06.346
hidden in your writer's room.

1:27:06.388 --> 1:27:08.765
Too many similarities between this made up story

1:27:08.807 --> 1:27:11.393
and the one going on in real life, wouldn't you say?

1:27:11.434 --> 1:27:13.520
No, this does not make sense!

1:27:13.562 --> 1:27:16.356
Anyone else have access to your work, Mrs. Morrison?

1:27:16.398 --> 1:27:19.026
Yes, of course, my publisher.

1:27:20.819 --> 1:27:23.321
-My husband. -You're so hot.

1:27:23.363 --> 1:27:25.448
Oh, and our nanny, Grace.

1:27:25.490 --> 1:27:28.577
[door opens] Mary, don't say another word.

1:27:31.121 --> 1:27:32.455
Oh, babe.

1:27:34.666 --> 1:27:36.877
Honey, I'm so sorry.

1:27:36.919 --> 1:27:39.088
It's all right, we're gonna figure this out.

1:27:39.129 --> 1:27:40.589
How is Rick doing?

1:27:41.673 --> 1:27:43.967
He's in shock.

1:27:44.009 --> 1:27:45.928
He doesn't think you did it, either.

1:27:47.971 --> 1:27:52.142
I don't understand how I'm the main suspect.

1:27:52.184 --> 1:27:54.603
Well, they don't have enough evidence to hold you.

1:27:54.644 --> 1:27:56.146
But what--

1:27:56.188 --> 1:27:58.398
What about the fingerprints on the scissors?

1:27:58.440 --> 1:28:01.068
Well, my fingerprints are on them, too.

1:28:01.110 --> 1:28:03.403
The kids' fingerprints are on the scissors.

1:28:04.404 --> 1:28:05.739
[sighs]

1:28:09.952 --> 1:28:11.245
Mary, where, um--

1:28:11.286 --> 1:28:13.496
Where-- Where were you last night?

1:28:14.873 --> 1:28:18.334
I-I got up to smoke...

1:28:18.376 --> 1:28:21.463
and then I saw that the light was on in my writer's room,

1:28:21.504 --> 1:28:22.965
so I went there to check.

1:28:23.006 --> 1:28:25.008
But nobody was there,

1:28:25.050 --> 1:28:28.720
and I locked it up and then I came back to bed.

1:28:32.766 --> 1:28:34.517
-You didn't go anywhere else? -Mm-mm.

1:28:34.559 --> 1:28:36.436
After you checked the house, you didn't--

1:28:36.478 --> 1:28:38.647
No. No, honey.

1:28:38.688 --> 1:28:41.024
You were gone for nearly three hours.

1:28:48.824 --> 1:28:50.909
Honey, really, I came right back to bed.

1:28:50.951 --> 1:28:52.619
You believe me, don't you?

1:28:55.413 --> 1:28:57.582
The slashed tires on the bike--

1:28:59.417 --> 1:29:01.920
They found a Swiss Army knife in the garage

1:29:01.962 --> 1:29:04.714
and the blade matches the markings on the bike tire.

1:29:04.756 --> 1:29:07.592
And yours are the only fingerprints on that knife.

1:29:12.139 --> 1:29:13.307
[clicks]

1:29:20.772 --> 1:29:22.357
When was the last time

1:29:22.398 --> 1:29:24.609
you were at Elaine's office for a session?

1:29:25.652 --> 1:29:27.112
Years ago.

1:29:28.655 --> 1:29:32.367
Well, they found some handwritten note that...

1:29:32.408 --> 1:29:33.785
seemed like a diagnosis,

1:29:33.827 --> 1:29:35.996
or that it outlined what you have.

1:29:36.038 --> 1:29:38.748
That is the time that I met her at the gym to work out.

1:29:38.790 --> 1:29:41.918
Those notes, they could be-- They could be about anyone.

1:29:44.213 --> 1:29:45.505
I know.

1:29:53.555 --> 1:29:56.892
[Grace, echoing] Who would do such a thing?

1:30:18.163 --> 1:30:19.413
Um...

1:30:21.041 --> 1:30:22.458
Uh...

1:30:22.500 --> 1:30:25.587
I've got to go to the restroom, okay?

1:30:29.966 --> 1:30:31.509
[footsteps fade]

1:30:39.559 --> 1:30:41.519
[tires squeal]

1:31:04.167 --> 1:31:06.211
[Tom] I told them you went home to rest.

1:31:06.253 --> 1:31:08.462
Really, I'm on my ass wanting to speak to you.

1:31:08.504 --> 1:31:10.048
Where are you?

1:31:15.387 --> 1:31:17.973
If you need something, if you're in trouble--

1:31:18.014 --> 1:31:19.391
I love you.

1:31:20.767 --> 1:31:22.894
[whispers] We can get you out.

1:31:22.936 --> 1:31:24.646
[normal voice] Meet you at home.

1:32:10.192 --> 1:32:11.525
[turns off engine]

1:32:17.991 --> 1:32:19.784
[dog barking]

1:32:21.286 --> 1:32:22.578
[sighs]

1:32:32.422 --> 1:32:34.216
[knocks]

